# What are the Russian supply lines to parts of occupied Luhansk region?

## Summary
The Russian supply lines to parts of occupied Luhansk regions have been under pressure in recent days as Ukrainian forces have pushed back in the eastern Kharkiv region. <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font> This led to Moscow ordering troops to leave the town of Svatove, a key link in the supply line, <font color=#FF3399>[2,3]</font> and the strategic city of Izium, which had been used as a launching pad and rail hub for attacks southwards, was taken by the Ukrainians. <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font> This was Moscow's worst defeat since their troops were forced back from Kyiv in March and was followed by the Russians having to abandon ammunition stockpiles and equipment. <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>

